{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/lanzar-comandos-de-la-terminal-al-abrir-un-proyecto-en-vs-code/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Estaba leyendo, como usualmente lo hago, los newsletters que me llegan al correo y en uno de esos me topé con un post de <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/some-little-improvements-to-my-vs-code-workflow-workspaces-icons-tasks/\">Chris Coyier en CSS Tricks</a> sobre su workflow en VS Code y me pareció interesante la parte en que hablaba de lanzar comandos de la terminal al abrir un proyecto, ya que uno siempre que abre un proyecto y tiene que correr el script <code class=\"language-text\">start</code> o <code class=\"language-text\">dev</code> o <code class=\"language-text\">watch</code> (o el que sea que utilices en tu proyecto) y es una buena forma de automatizar tu workflow ☝️ así que aquí se los comparto!</p>\n<h2 id=\"tasks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tasks\" aria-label=\"tasks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tasks</h2>\n<p>Para eso se han implementado las tareas. Puedes crearlas de dos formas: Manualmente o desde el menu.</p>\n<h3 id=\"manualmente\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#manualmente\" aria-label=\"manualmente permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Manualmente</h3>\n<p>Para hacerlo manualmente solo tienes que crear tu archivo <code class=\"language-text\">tasks.json</code> dentro de la carpeta <code class=\"language-text\">.vscode</code> y agregar las propiedades que necesites según la <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/tasks\">documentación</a> 👀</p>\n<h3 id=\"desde-el-menú\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#desde-el-men%C3%BA\" aria-label=\"desde el menú permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Desde el menú</h3>\n<p>La otra opción es seleccionar la opción Configure Tasks o Configure Default Build Task desde el menú Terminal, dependiendo de lo que necesites. Eso mostrará un dropdown para selecionar las tareas escaneadas en tu proyecto. Algo como esto:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fRzPqKE.png\" alt=\"Terminal 👉 Configure Tasks\"></p>\n<p>Al seleccionar una te creará el archivo <code class=\"language-text\">tasks.json</code> dentro de la carpeta <code class=\"language-text\">.vscode</code>. En mi caso:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-json line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"version\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"2.0.0\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"tasks\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"type\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"npm\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"script\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"dev\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"problemMatcher\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"label\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"npm: dev\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"detail\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby develop\"</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>El cual puedes modificar según tus necesidades siguiendo la <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/tasks\">documentación</a>.</p>\n<p>En mi caso yo le agregué estas líneas:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-json line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"version\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"2.0.0\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"tasks\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"type\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"npm\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"script\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"dev\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"problemMatcher\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"label\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"npm: dev\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">\"detail\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby develop\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token property\">\"presentation\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token property\">\"panel\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"shared\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token property\">\"showReuseMessage\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token property\">\"clear\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token property\">\"runOptions\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token property\">\"runOn\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"folderOpen\"</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span>    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Para que no abriera una nueva terminal cada vez que se ejecute la tarea y para que la tarea se lance automáticamente cuando abra el folder en VS Code. Para que suceda esto último (que la tarea automáticamente), la primera vez tienes que lanzarla manualmente (Terminal 👉 Run Task), para que tenga los permisos correctos, entonces funciona automáticamente a partir de ahí ✌️😁</p>\n<p>That's all folks!</p>","excerpt":"Estaba leyendo, como usualmente lo hago, los newsletters que me llegan al correo y en uno de esos me topé con un post de Chris Coyier en CSS…","fields":{"slug":"/lanzar-comandos-de-la-terminal-al-abrir-un-proyecto-en-vs-code/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Lanzar comandos de la terminal al abrir un proyecto en VS Code","date":"May 02, 2020","tags":["vscode"],"description":null,"banner":"https://i.imgur.com/CEnh8Y6.png","slug":"lanzar-comandos-de-la-terminal-al-abrir-un-proyecto-en-vs-code"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/lanzar-comandos-de-la-terminal-al-abrir-un-proyecto-en-vs-code/","previous":{"id":"075b1e8b-b92b-5c39-93d3-89a027563869","frontmatter":{"title":"Cómo sobrevivo al distanciamiento social","banner":"https://i.imgur.com/rWJBs40.jpg","categories":["JesusFreak"],"tags":["cuarentena","Paul Tripp"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/como-sobrevivo-al-distanciamiento-social/"}},"next":{"id":"095dd8ad-6119-579a-a8f2-bfa7d4abc4e4","frontmatter":{"title":"Cómo probar un paquete npm localmente","banner":"https://i.imgur.com/XJHiNhx.png","categories":["Code"],"tags":["npm","link","node","yalc"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/como-probar-un-paquete-npm-localmente/"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}